commit: 21557bbb + dispatch-cadence bench
host:   AMD Ryzen 9 7950X (Zen 4, AVX2)
cmd:    cargo bench --bench deinterleave --features experimental -- --group="dispatch cadence"
date:   2026-04-29 UTC

Bench shape:
  Total work fixed at 64K f32 RGB pixels (~1.5 MB working set, L2-resident).
  Sweep chunk size from 8 → 8192 pixels per call.
  A: dispatch-per-chunk — outer scalar loop calls rgb_f32_to_planes_f32()
     per chunk, each call going through #[arcane] AVX2 dispatch.
  B: autovec-whole-loop — outer loop wrapped in a single #[arcane] AVX2
     region, inner = scalar_only_* (which inlines into the AVX2 region
     and gets autovectorized).

Per-call dispatch overhead (delta_time / num_calls):
  chunk=8     8K calls, 75.3 µs delta → ~9 ns/call
  chunk=32    2K calls, 15.8 µs delta → ~7.7 ns/call
  chunk=128   512 calls, 1.7 µs delta → ~3.3 ns/call (within noise)
  chunk≥512   negligible (within bench noise)

Practical breakeven: ~128 pixels per call. Below that, hoist the dispatch
outside the loop. Above that, per-call dispatch is invisible.
